					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Early Abashi news posts</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=169771" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/058870.html">why WALK Abashi?</a></B><P>

Why do we even have the option to walk? Everyone agrees that the toggle should be set to RUN as a default, but why do we even have the option to move at a slower speed?<P>

<B>We're still clinging to the idea that people might decide to walk from time to time as a matter of roleplay, hence, your character walks until it *decides* to run. Is it really that difficult to hit a few buttons when logging on?<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/059259.html">I dare Abashi to put up a death penalty poll</a></B><P>

I can guarantee that you will see that most of your player base will want it reduced.<P>

<B>I'll have to pass. We only put up polls on issues that we are somewhat flexible on. The death penalty is not one of those issues. The penalty is necessary in order for there to be challenge in the game. If that penalty is too severe, then people have the option to get someone to resurrect them. If that penalty is too severe, and people don't want to have to rely on clerics or high-level paladins for resurrections, they have the option to not adventure in places where the risk of death is that high. <P>

Lastly, if it is too severe, and they don't want to rely on cleris or high-level paladins to reduce the penalty, and they still want to adventure in areas where the risk of dying is high, I'm sorry, but the penalty is something that people will have to deal with. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/059335.html">Pumice: Verant please confirm/deny</a></B><P>

I realize that the "pumice" change may have been a "vision" move, however, where's the official statement about it?<P>

<B>There wasn't supposed to be an official announcement before-hand. The existing item wasn't changed, but rather, the vendors just sell a different item now. The original pumice stone is still in game, and in fact, drops someplace as loot now.<P>

That said, I'm assuming you want to know why it was done. Frankly, purchased items should generally not be more efficient than casting the spell yourself or getting someone else to cast it upon you.<P> 

-Gordon</b>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
