hit the RUN key when you log on.  The problem I have <BR>
With the default, is the EQ propensity to crash, <BR>
often in the middle of a  hairy battle, back to desktop<BR>
In the last eight months, everyone I have grouped with <BR>
On the Veeshan server, has had the crashing problem, save<BR>
for a 2 week period in May 2000.  With the next patch, <BR>
the problem was re-introduced, and We can't play for any <BR>
ten minute period without someone, and often half of the <BR>
group going linkdead.  When you log back in to a fully <BR>
spawned camp in some dungeon, where everyone that didn't <BR>
crash or die has run to the zone, it's those 2 precious<BR>
seconds of leadtime on the mobs that can mean the difference<BR>
between life, and having to spend 2 more days making up the<BR>
lost experience of death that COULD have been prevented by changing a <BR>
stupid default.  Walking definitely has it's place and advantages from <BR>
time to time, but make the default run.  We can always change it<BR>
when we need to, and while you're at it fix the dang crashing problem.<BR>
I've done all the stuff recommended to fix, many times, and removed, <BR>
and reinstalled the game several times.  Other than the 2 week time period<BR>
in May, there has been no improvement.<BR>
