	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Lets see...<BR>
<BR>
100,000 people taking 2 seconds to switch from walk to run mode (say) once a week..<BR>
<BR>
Plus (my pet peeve) 15 seconds wasted trying to exit the damn game (WHY OH WHY DO I HAVE TO GO THROUGH FOUR DIALOGS TO EXIT???)...<BR>
<BR>
Say 1.7 million seconds a week.  472 hours of our time spent doing un-fun stuff every week.<BR>
<BR>
I won't even count the minute or two going through the login process (OK, I'm happy there wasn't a patch today.  Yes, I agree Yet Again to sacrifice my first-born son to your lawyers.  Yes, Verant and Sony have very pretty logos.  Yes, I want to play on the same server I played on yesterday.  Yes, I want to play the same character I played yesterday.)<BR>
<BR>
Come on, you say you want to make the game more appealing to casual gamers.  Guess what?  These little niggling startup/shutdown issues are a much bigger deal for people who play for 20 minutes here, an hour there (powergamers who logon at 6PM and logout at 1AM every day probably don't care...).<BR>
<BR>
So:<BR>
<BR>
Make run the default.  (plane-walkers can change it)<BR>
<BR>
Make the login process faster.  How about a &quot;Quick Login&quot; button the second time you play, after the patch download, that logins to the same server and character played last time?<BR>
<BR>
Make the logout process faster.  How about a &quot;/quit&quot; command that makes you sit down, start camping, and then immediately exits completely all the way out.<BR>
<BR>
Just think of the return on investment: get a programmer to spend 40 hours, and save your customers over 20,000 hours of their valuable time a year!<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
